  "steps": [
    "Heat a pressure cooker, add brown Bengal grams, salt, 1 teaspoon dried mango powder, 1 teaspoon coriander powder, ½ teaspoon red chilli powder and 3½ cups water and mix well.",
    "Close the cooker and cook under pressure on medium heat till the pressure is released 3-4 times.",
    "Open the lid once the pressure settles completely. Strain and keep the grams and the stock separately.",
    "Heat mustard oil in a non-stick kadai till it begins to smoke then add asafoetida and cumin seeds and mix. Once cumin seeds start to change colour, add fennel seeds and fenugreek seeds, mix and sauté for 30 seconds.",
    "Add dried red chillies and mix well. Add turmeric powder, remaining red chilli powder, remaining coriander powder, remaining dried mango powder, rice flour, gram flour and salt, mix well and sauté on low heat for 2-3 minutes.",
    "Add boiled grams, mix well and sauté for 4-5 minutes.",
    "Add cooking stock, mix well and cook on medium heat till mixture thickens.",
    "Add garam masala powder, mint leaves and jaggery, mix well and cook till jaggery melts.",
    "Transfer into a serving bowl, garnish with coriander sprig and serve hot with steamed rice."
  ],
